title: Bug 49235ServletContainerInitializer onStartup(Set<Class<? classSet is not expected class
OB: The output is 'MySomeClass', but I expect the output to be 'MySomeClass'. It is not yet implemented in the Servlet 3.0 spec. My code works fine on Glassfish 3.0.
EB: The classSet should not be an expected class.
SR: To reproduce the issue, call the onStartup method of the ServletContainerInitializer with a set containing a Class object.
